Bulgaria is looking for investors to
lease airports in the countryâ€™s second-biggest cit, Plovdiv, and
the Danube River port of Rousse,  Dnevnik  reported, citing deputy
Transport Minister Kamen Kichev.  Bids for a 35-year lease involving construction of a cargo
terminal, office building and a hangar will be opened on June 6,
the newspaper said. Bids for the Rousse airport, which needs
investment of some 43 million lev ($31.3 million) to upgrade the
passenger terminal and build a cargo terminal, will be opened on
June 17, Dnevnik said. Both airports can be used by low-cost
airlines, according to Dnevnik.  To contact the reporter on this story:
